Description: Copper alloy amuletic figure of an ibis upon a triangular base, with a vertical suspension loop behind the neck, connected to the rear of the base by a tang.
Curator's comments: Possibly the bronze figure of "Tahuti", or one of the "sacred animals" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.49, p.62, p.180, pl.22)
